        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "Estimating questions' difficulty levels is an important task in community question answering ( CQA ) services . <S>",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Previous studies propose to solve this problem based on the question-user comparisons ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "extracted from the question answering threads . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "However , they suffer from data sparseness problem ",
            "relation": "CONTRAST"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "as each question only gets a limited number of comparisons . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT-REASON"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "Moreover , they cannot handle newly posted questions ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "which get no comparisons . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "In this paper , we propose a novel question difficulty estimation approach ",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "called Regularized Competition Model ( RCM ) , ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "which naturally combines question-user comparisons and questions' textual descriptions into a unified framework . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "By incorporating textual information , ",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "RCM can effectively deal with data sparseness problem . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "We further employ a K-Nearest Neighbor approach ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "to estimate difficulty levels of newly posted questions , ",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "again by leveraging textual similarities . <S>",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "Experiments on two publicly available data sets show ",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 16,
            "text": "that for both well-resolved and newly-posted questions , RCM performs the estimation task significantly better than existing methods , ",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "demonstrating the advantage of incorporating textual information . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 19,
            "parent": 16,
            "text": "More interestingly , we observe ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 20,
            "parent": 19,
            "text": "that RCM might provide an automatic way ",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 21,
            "parent": 20,
            "text": "to quantitatively measure the knowledge levels of words . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        }
    ]
